Class Range

  • java.lang.Object
    • eecs2030.lab0.Range

  • public class Range
extends Object
    A class that represents a range of values on the real number line. A range has two properties: a minimum value and a maximum value. Range objects always ensure that the following class invariant is true:

    minimum <= maximum

    The constructors of the class are responsible for ensuring that the above class invariant is always true.

    Author:
    EECS2030 Winter 2019-2020

      • toString

        public String toString()
        Returns the string representation of a range. The string contains the minimum and maximum values separated by a comma and space all inside of a pair of square brackets. For example, the string

        [-3.14, 3.14]

        represents the range whose minimum value is -3.14 and whose maximum value is 3.14
